# CLI command structure

Applies to every command under **`apps/<name>/`**.

## Layers

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
|-------|----------|----------------|
| Entry | `apps/<name>/src/cli.ts` | `runMain(command)` only |
| Citty tree | `apps/<name>/src/command.ts`, `src/commands/**` | `define<App>Command`, args schema, routing |
| Parse | `packages/<name>/options.ts` | `parse<Command>Options(args)` → typed options |
| Execute | `packages/<name>/main.ts` | `run<Command>(options)` — no citty, no argv |

## Required pattern

citty `run` must be thin — parse, then execute:

```typescript
run: defineCommandRunner(parseValidateBatchOptions, runValidateBatch),
```

Or explicitly:

```typescript
async run({ args }) {
  await runValidateBatch(parseValidateBatchOptions(args));
},
```

**Forbidden in `run`:** `Bun.spawn`, file I/O, network, or business logic.
Those belong in `packages/<name>/main.ts`.

## Callable API

Export `run*` and `parse*` from the companion package so other apps and
tests invoke commands without citty:

```typescript
import { runValidateBatch } from "@univocity-tools/builder-common/main";
await runValidateBatch({
  path: "/abs/batch.json",
  verbose: true,
  univocityRoot: "/abs/univocity",
  forgeConfig: "/abs/univocity/foundry.toml",
});
```

Builder merges the **forge options mixin** — typed options include
absolute `univocityRoot` (contracts checkout root) and `forgeConfig`.

Full guide: [docs/agents/cli.md](../../docs/agents/cli.md).
